          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684417333845-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>couscous</strong> to a large heatproof bowl with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> half </strong>the <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>sultanas</strong>,<strong> diced apricots </strong>and the <strong>diced shallot</strong></p><p>Add a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then give everything a good mix up until fully combined</p><p>Add 130ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[260ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>cover and set aside until all of the liquid has been absorbed</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684417383776-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684417383776-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684417383776-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684417383776-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684417383776-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>feta</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> in a small bowl with 40ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[60ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and whisk until thickened to a sauce-like consistency – this is your <strong>whipped feta sauce</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>harissa </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]<strong> </span>butter </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>harissa butter</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684418615392-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684418615392-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684418615392-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684418615392-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684418615392-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the liquid has been absorbed, fluff the <strong>couscous</strong> with a fork</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach </strong>and<strong> </strong>most of the<strong> chopped parsley </strong>(save some for garnish!) – this is your <strong>fruity couscous</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1684417970154-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1684417970154-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1684417970154-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1684417970154-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1684417970154-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the cabbage has had an initial 25-30 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and discard the foil</p><p>Squeeze the juice of the <strong>orange[s]</strong> over the roasted cabbage</p><p>Top with the <strong>harissa butter</strong>, then return the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to the oven and cook for 3-4 min or until the butter has melted – this is your <strong>charred harissa cabbage</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1684417973587-x200.jpg",
